value.0: Dogma of Kurtulmak: The kobolds are a great race, worthy to take their place among (or even dominate) the other races of the world.  There is no shame in being small and short; indeed being of such stature can be used to advantage when dealing with taller races.  Destroy all gnomes, for not only are they the rivals of the kobold people, but Kurtulmak demands revenge for all the humiliations he has suffered at the hands of their gods.  Stay united, for only in unity can enemies be defeated and the kobold race rise to their destiny.
In death, the face of the bare-chested man seems frozen with fear. You wonder what it was that killed him.

A gleam of iron...
